<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB: 5000, 9100, 9200, 9300, 9400 - ADJUSTMENTS - STRIKER
        PIN AT LOCK PILLAR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1600510" svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>STRIKER PIN AT LOCK PILLAR</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f16005b4">Figure 114</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <figure id="f16005b4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/G1600593.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 114. Door Striker Pin</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. LOCK PILLAR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DOOR STRIKER PIN 34 TO 50 FT-LBS. (46 TO 68 Nm)</callout1>
                <callout1>3. TORX HEAD TOOL</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SPACER SHIM</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a torx head tool (Item 3) and loosen striker pin (Item 2) to move pin up or down and
                forward or back as required.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">In and out adjustment of striker pin (Item 2) is done with spacer shims (Item 4) between
                striker pin and lock pillar (Item 1). Remove striker pin and add or remove spacer shims as required.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make final adjustment of striker pin (Item 2) and tighten to 34 to 50 ft-lbs. (46 to 68
                Nm).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
